description.narrative: In 2020, the Country Office supported the development of a common, coordinated vision for child protection within line Ministries and development partners. Social services continued to receive direct cash transfers for the prevention and care of child victims of violence, abuse, and exploitation. Thanks to this support, children who were displaced during the COVID-19 pandemic and the electoral period could be immediately assisted. A national mobilization campaign titled “Reimagining Côte d’Ivoire without violence against children”was launched under the presidency of the First Lady of Côte d&39;Ivoire. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:19/01/2021
